## Create EKS cluster manually using eksctl


```bash
eksctl create cluster \
  --name my-eks-cluster \
  --region ap-south-1 \
  --nodegroup-name workers \
  --node-type t3.medium \
  --nodes 2 \
  --nodes-min 1 \
  --nodes-max 3 \
  --managed
```

**Update kubeconfig:**

```bash
aws eks update-kubeconfig --region ap-south-1 --name my-eks-cluster
```
**Verify cluster:**

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```

